# Git commits: no Cursor attribution

- Do **not** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Co-authored-by: cursoragent@cursor.com`, or any Cursor/Changelog footer to commit messages.
- Do **not** list Cursor as a contributor in commit trailers or GitHub co-author metadata.
- When creating commits in this repo, use **`git commit --no-verify`** only if a local hook incorrectly injects Cursor co-author lines; prefer fixing the hook so normal commits stay valid.

Human authors own authorship; AI assistance must not appear in `git log` or GitHub contributor attribution.
